# Paths excluded from the tgz ArgoCD streams to CMP plugins (e.g. ksops)
# during repository discovery (MatchRepository). Without this, the ~46 MB
# working tree causes the ksops sidecar's 60s gRPC deadline to be exceeded,
# resulting in "could not find cmp-server plugin with name ksops".
#
# Rule: only exclude directories that are NOT ArgoCD-managed source paths.
# ArgoCD-managed paths (apps/homepage/, platform/**) must remain visible.

# Not ArgoCD-managed: manual k8s install scripts + kubeadm configs (~29 MB)
infrastructure/

# Not ArgoCD-managed: chat-app source code + static assets (~16 MB)
# chat-app/k8s/ raw manifests are applied by hand, not via an Application.
apps/chat-app/

# Not ArgoCD-managed: Ansible / Jenkins config management
automation/
